ds and they’re so easy.\n\n<img class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-147\" src=\"http://localhost:8888/foxesden/wp-content/uploads/2017/07/810-2-1.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"810\" height=\"540\" />\n<h2>On her beauty inspirations</h2>\nMy whole family is basically women and my grandmother is a Southern woman who will not go out of the house without her make-up on. So I’ve been watching her beauty regime my whole life. She removes her make-up with Vaseline! She was, like, the most excited of everyone about the L’Oréal partnership. She only uses L’Oréal lipsticks and they have such a specific smell, so they really remind me of her and of going through her make-up drawer.\n\n<aside class=\"ad__main is-hidden ad--article ad--article-inline \">\n<div class=\"ad__block \"> <img class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-146\" src=\"http://localhost:8888/foxesden/wp-content/uploads/2017/07/810-3-1.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"810\" height=\"1215\" /></div>\n</aside>\n<h2>On hair</h2>\nI really try to take good care of my hair. I have dyed it a lot of different colours which can be scary as you don’t want to ruin it. It’s hard to keep it in good form. I’ve had it pink, and red and brunette... I like to experiment but it’s important to keep it healthy so I’ll do masks at night.\n<h2>On L’Oréal Paris</h2>\nIt feels incredible to be an ambassador. I mean, I feel really proud to be part of such a fantastic family of women who are so strong. And the brand’s message is so important for women and young girls – being worth it and loving yourself and not being afraid to stand out from the crowd and accepting all your differences... I think it’s very important. Susan Sarandon and I did a movie together and she is the most beautiful, sexy, cool woman. Julianne Moore I’d never met until Cannes, but she was so nice - they’re all so nice and I respect them so much, they represent everything that the L’Oréal brand is.\n<h2>On the red carpet</h2>\nI get really pumped up for the red carpet. Yes, you get a little bit nervous – it’s a whole mixture of emotions – but it’s exciting. If you have jet lag then it just completely goes away. And I love getting dressed up. I have to stand out from the crowd, I don’t want to blend in with everyone else. And for things like Cannes I’ll take into account things like the stairs – so I’ll think about the back of the dress because photographers are on either side of you. You have to think about all angles. I like to play up old Hollywood glamour.\n\n<hr />\n\n<ul>\n 	<li>One</li>\n 	<li>Two</li>\n 	<li>Three</li>\n</ul>\nFour\n\nOne\n\nTwo\n\nThree\n\nFour\n<h2>On fitness</h2>\nI do more fitness stuff when I’m at home and it’s part of my daily routine, because that’s so much easier. I did ballet for a long time – that’s the best form of exercise. It’s elongating. And I’ve started boxing recently, which is really fun.\n<h2>On pampering</h2>\nTo relax I take a lot of baths. If I’m washing my hair then I’ll have a shower, but every night I pretty much take a tub. It’s a quiet moment. If I’m getting fancy I’ll do candles.\n\n<aside class=\"a-sidebar-content\">&nbsp;\n\n<article class=\"c-card c-card--portrait-small\">\n<div class=\"c-card__obj\"></div>\n</article></aside>\n<h2>On her career</h2>\nI love my job because I get to transform into other characters and travel and meet so many different people. It’s really stimulating and inspiring - it’s something that I hope is in my life forever. In the future I’d love to direct, it’s something I’d really like to do in the future and something to look forward to. I also really want to do a movie with my sister. We’ve never done that! But it would have to be perfect. It’d be fun to do one with Dakota and Sofia Coppola, and with Kirsten Dunst because she’s basically like the honorary Fanning sister. Literally, she’s both of our big sister. So if all four of us could do something… Kirsten and I really want to do a comedy together so if we all did some crazy comedy that could be so funny.', 'On Beauty: Elle Fanning', 'Here, Fanning talks to Vogue about her skincare regime, the beauty tricks she learned from her grandmother and her career goals for the future.', 'inherit', 'closed', 'closed', '', '144-autosave-v1', '', '', '2017-07-18 02:52:11', '2017-07-18 02:52:11', '', 144, 'http://localhost:8888/foxesden/144-autosave-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
