(178, 1, '2017-07-18 03:42:39', '2017-07-18 03:42:39', '<span class=\"bb-dropcap bb-dropcap--letter\">B</span>efore we begin, we should note that the most impressive thing Venus Williams showcased in the <a href=\"http://www.vogue.co.uk/gallery/wimbledon-celebrities-2017\">Wimbledon 2017</a> final yesterday was the tennis skills that have previously won her seven grand slam and 49 WTA singles titles. But the next most impressive thing? Her absolutely and completely water-proof, smudge-proof and <a href=\"http://www.vogue.co.uk/gallery/what-is-athleisure-beauty-anyway\">sweat-proof </a>eyeliner.\r\n\r\nYes, Spain’s Garbiñe Muguruza may have beaten the American tennis star to the women’s singles title at Wimbledon 2017, but Williams was undeniably the all-round winner when it came to her indestructible make-up. She sweated, she shed tears and she wiped her face roughly with a towel, but even when her serve let her down, her eyeliner stayed put.\r\n\r\n<img class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-180\" src=\"http://localhost:8888/foxesden/wp-content/uploads/2017/07/810-8.jpeg\" alt=\"\" width=\"810\" height=\"869\" />\r\n\r\nTwitter, naturally, was all over it. “LOVE that Venus Williams played in absolute fuck-off girl group eyeliner. Boss,” tweeted writer Caitlin Moran, whilst The Guardian’s running blog editor – who surely knows a thing or two about the effects of sweat on make-up – concurred, saying: “Venus Williams may be a set and two breaks down but her eyeliner game is still remarkable.”\r\n\r\n<img class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-179\" src=\"http://localhost:8888/foxesden/wp-content/uploads/2017/07/810-7.jpeg\" alt=\"\" width=\"810\" height=\"540\" />\r\n\r\nBut which eyeliner does she use? Williams has credited Milani’s Infinite Liquid Eye Liner with her on-court beauty look, and applies it in a graphic winged swoop extending from both the upper and lower lash lines. She is also a frequent wearer of nail polish on the court, choosing a glossy black for the Wimbledon final.\r\n\r\nWe’ve told you before about <a href=\"http://www.vogue.co.uk/article/why-wearing-make-up-to-work-out-exercise-is-bad-for-skin\">why exercising in make-up is bad</a>, but since Williams was on international television at the time, and carried off her tennis-court beauty regime with such aplomb, we’ll give her a free pass. Perhaps not the winner of the Venus Rosewater Dish this year, but certainly the winner of the eyeliner championships.\r\n<h2>10 Best Liquid Eyeliners</h2>\r\n&nbsp;', 'An Ode To Venus Williams\'s Eyeliner', 'We talk about her absolutely and completely water-proof, smudge-proof and sweat-proof eyeliner.', 'publish', 'closed', 'open', '', 'an-ode-to-venus-williamss-eyeliner', '', '', '2017-07-20 05:07:43', '2017-07-20 05:07:43', '', 0, 'http://localhost:8888/foxesden/?post_type=beauty-post&#038;p=178', 0, 'beauty-post', '', 0),
